      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 43
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a benchmark in high-performance engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS system to achieve a remarkable power-to-displacement ratio. The power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission, delivering drive to the rear wheels through a variable M-differential lock. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive cooling system refresh. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, and the suspension bushings have been replaced to ensure precise turn-in and lateral stability. While the aesthetics show light signs of use, the drivetrain and internal mechanical components are in peak operating condition, offering an uncompromised analog driving experience.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 43
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
